<b>(iii)</b>	Use scale(s) to represent the values of variables on the table of values on the graph e.g. from the table of values in step (ii), you may use; 1cm to 1min on the horizontal axis (x-axis) and 1cm to 50m on the vertical axis (y-axis). It is important to choose large scale when drawing graphs.
<br>
<strong>Note;</strong> scale of a graph is the ratio representing a value on an axis or a ratio comparing the actual lengths to those on a drawing.
<br>
<b>(iv)</b>	Connect all the ordered pair points on the graph to have a continuous line.
<br>
<b>(v)</b>	Name the two axes and give a title to the graph.
